Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza In Romania: Follow-up report No. 4
---------------------------------------------------------------
Information received on 22 Oct 2005 from Dr Gabriel Predoi, Director
General, National Sanitary Veterinary and Food Safety Authority, Bucharest:
End of previous report period: 20 Oct 2005
End of this report period: 22 Oct 2005.
Precise identification of agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus
subtype H5N1.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 7 Oct 2005.
Date of start of the event: 4 Oct 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Details of new outbreak:
First administrative division (County): Vaslui
Lower administrative division (district): Falciu
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: in the vicinity of the village of Falciu
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Oct. 2005
Species: fau (Heron)
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
-- / 1/ 1 / -- / --
Description of affected population in the new outbreak: a heron was found
dead in an unpopulated area, at a distance of about 700 m from Prut River,
close to the international border with Moldavia; the heron may have
belonged to a flock of migratory birds.
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Institute for Diagnostics
and Animal Health (national reference laboratory for avian influenza)
Animals examined: 1 heron
Diagnostic tests used: virus isolation
Date: 21 Oct 2005
Results: positive for virus subtype H5
Source of new outbreak: unknown or inconclusive.
Final report: no.
